<subSubSection id="0A74B9E7982783D628D1EB85D17E6450" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="111" pageId="19" pageNumber="110" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F26EC5877F39E9D28BE88C6953A4DA65" pageId="19" pageNumber="110">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2359B6020AE4E9B75BD31AB1D5EAED4" pageId="19" pageNumber="110">
This species was previously recorded from Guatemala (
<bibRefCitation id="403604E59B3533E32A39FA177EAB57FF" author="Howden, HF" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada" pageId="30" pageNumber="121" pagination="1 - 77" title="A review of the Trichiinae of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae)." url="10.4039/entm10054fv" volume="54" year="1968">Howden 1968</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens detailed below represent a new country record for Mexico. The Mexican specimens have some variation in the metathoracic leg characters and setal characters that bear further investigation.
</paragraph>
